 <!--

--> Since ancient time, lion has been believed to an auspicious animal, hence lion dance is staged on big occasions for good luck, such as the Chinese New Year. As an old Chinese saying goes, "One minute on the stage, ten years of practice off the stage." Watch the video to see how actors practice this traditional performance behind the scene. Video credit to "Mr. Liao" (Douyin#liaoshifu888), posted on Chinese online video-sharing platform Douyin (the Chinese version of TikTok). (Source: Douyin)  